Console Piano:
A console piano program written in C# using NAudio.
The program lets the  user play piano notes through keyboard inputs and has adjust settings while program is running.

Features:
play piano notes using the keyboard
Hold shift for black keys
switch between multiple sound fonts
Adjust volume, transposition, and sustain
supports playing many notes at once

Controls:
Notes 1-0, Q-P, A-L, Z-M
Black keys: hold shift while playing a note
Control volume with left arrow/ right arrow
Control tranpose with up arrow/ down arrow
Control sustain with space bar
Change soundfont with [ / ]
To quit the program press esc

Soundfonts:
To add more soundfonts grab a soundfont from this repository: https://github.com/gleitz/midi-js-soundfonts/tree/gh-pages/MusyngKite
Then add it to the sounds folder.

How to run:
Clone the repository
make sure the sounds folder has at least one soundfont
run the program

Design:
uses multiple classes with clear responsibilites
Encapsulation is enforced using private fields
Inheritance is used through a base PianoSetting class
Polymorphism is demonstrated by overriding methods in derived setting classes